    "body": "Hey @mexicanpepe. Looks like there is something wrong with the way npm is configured. The directory where it installs globally-installed packages needs to be in your `$PATH` variable. I usually recommend re-installing npm and Node with a Node version manager like nvm which is what npm recommends. You can check out [this article](https://docs.npmjs.com/resolving-eacces-permissions-errors-when-installing-packages-globally). This hopefully will correctly add the necessary director(y|ies). Let me know how it goes.",
